  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is typically legally defined as the process of concealing the origins of illegally obtained money by passing it through complex transactions or legitimate businesses. Key elements usually include:\n\n1. Generally includes three main stages:\n- Placement (introducing illegal funds into financial system)\n- Layering (disguising the source through complex transactions)\n- Integration (making funds appear legitimate)\n\n2. Common legal elements include:\n- Knowingly concealing the source of funds\n- Attempting to make illegal money appear legal\n- Engaging in financial transactions to hide criminal proceeds\n- Transferring money to obscure its illegal origin\n\n3. Specific activities often considered money laundering:\n- Structuring bank deposits to avoid reporting requirements\n- Using shell companies\n- Complex international wire transfers\n- Converting cash into other financial instruments\n\n4. Typically requires:\n- Intent to conceal\n- Knowledge that funds are from criminal activity\n- Deliberate attempt to make funds seem legitimate\n\nPlease note that precise definitions can vary between jurisdictions. Consulting local legal statutes is recommended for specific details.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these points?",
